.TH "rpc_sockaddr2uaddr" 9 "rpc_sockaddr2uaddr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpc_sockaddr2uaddr \- Construct a universal address string from @sap.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" rpc_sockaddr2uaddr
.BI "(const struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sap" 12
socket address
.IP "gfp_flags" 12
allocation mode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a NUL-terminated string in dynamically allocated memory;
otherwise NULL is returned if an error occurred.  Caller must
free the returned string.
